<title>USA: Health Management to defend lawsuits.</title>
<headline>Health Management to defend lawsuits.</headline>
<dateline>NEW YORK 1997-04-02</dateline>
<text>
<p>Health Management Systems Inc said on Wednesday that it will defend itself from two purported class action lawsuits that have been filed against the company and certain officers and directors.</p>
<p>The lawsuits, which are pending in the U.S District Court for the Southern District of New York, allege violations of the Securities and Exchange Act of 1934, Health Management said.</p>
<p>Health Management said it has retained Jonathan Lerner of the law firm of Skadden, Arps, Slate, Meagher &amp; Flom LLP to represent the company in the defense of these actions.</p>
